text:
Great value for the price. 
Pros:
- friendly service;
- super cozy and well equipped rooms;
- great views;
- good price and convenient location.

However, there are some cons:
- elevator traffic;
- the door to the bathroom was broken and we were not able to close it. We asked a front desk officer to send someone to fix it on the first day of our stay, but nobody ever came.

My wife and I recently stayed at the Fairfield Inn & Suites New York Manhattan/Times Square hotel and had the most wonderful time!

From the moment we walked into the hotel to check in on Friday, through to the very end when we left Monday late afternoon to catch our flight home, we were greeted, welcomed, serviced, and helped by the warmest, most sincere and helpful hotel employees I have seen in a long time. This included Whitney who was super warm and bubbly throughout our check in and had a hand, amongst others, in arranging birthday cupcakes in our room upon arrival for my birthday, and Anthony who was so helpful while we struggled to print our show tickets purchased on Stubhub. Other friendly employees included the bell men, other front desk team members and the lovely team members who made sure we were well fed at the included breakfast each morning.

The hotel is extremely conveniently located within easy walking distance to all the Broadway Theatres, Times Square, The High Line Park (definitely worth some time to see and enjoy on a nice day), and many restaurants.

We were lucky enough to have a beautiful, large, 1 bedroom suite on the top floor of the hotel with great views. The room was very modern and extremely well kept with a beautiful, well lit bathroom and an extremely comfortable king sized bed. Although we did not spend much time in the room, it was a pleasure to be in to relax after long days out and about in NYC.

Additional positive comments to share about the hotel:
·   the lobby has cold refreshing water to drink as you come in from the hot summer weather;
·   the hotel provides guests with free water bottles in your room, which you can take with you when you go out for long treks in the city;
·   we loved the Starbucks coffee available throughout the day in the lobby;
·   the included breakfast each morning was perfect! Fresh fruit, yogurt, breads/bagels, eggs, sausages and much more. To go boxes available if you wanted to eat in the privacy of your own room. 

All in all, a really wonderful stay at this great hotel with an exceptional team of staff members. We would stay again in a heartbeat!
